   "source": [
    "reachy.turn_on()\n",
    "\n",
    "reachy.goto_posture('default')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "`goto_posture()` is a convenient function to configure the posture of all Reachy parts at once. \n",
    "\n",
    "It accepts the parameters : \n",
    "- *default* (i.e. `goto_posture('default')`), which gives Reachy's default pose with arms outstretched on either side of the body,\n",
    "- *elbow_90* (i.e. `goto_posture('elbow_90')`), in which Reachy has the two forearms parallel to the ground. \n",
    "\n",
    "These standard poses can be useful when you want to start a new task from a known position."
   ]
